  "body": "#### Feature Description\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/vitessio/vitess/pull/5419 I added a check to see if the user was root, and bail.\r\n\r\nThis relies on the user using the included shell script, which adds complexity and a bit annoying if the user wants to roll their own scripts around standalone vitess binaries.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice enhancement if `mysqlctl` itself (and possibly other components) checked if the user is root, and refused to start.",
